# D365 F&O Security

Microsoft source: [Security architecture](https://learn.microsoft.com/dynamics365/fin-ops-core/dev-itpro/sysadmin/security-architecture)

## Core rules

- **Roles → Duties → Privileges → Permissions**
- Secure every new **entry point**
- **Least privilege** — no System Administrator for routine work
- **Duplicate** standard roles — never modify standard artifacts
- **TPF** for sensitive fields; **XDS** for row-level (performance-test queries)

## Scenarios and recommendations

### New menu item (display or action)

**Recommend:** Create **Privilege** with menu item permission → add to **Duty** → assign Duty to **Role** (not 40 privileges on role directly).

**Avoid:** Menu item with no privilege mapping; granting SysAdmin to test quickly.

### New SysOperation / service entry point

**Recommend:** Same as menu item — map privilege to service/class entry; document required duty in implementation guide.

**Avoid:** Callable service only from code with no security artifact for ops team.

### OData exposure of data entity

**Recommend:** Entity permission with integration mode **DataServices** (or **All** if both DMF and OData needed).

**Avoid:** Integration mode **All** when only OData is required (over-exposure).

### DMF import/export only

**Recommend:** Integration mode **DataManagement** on entity permission.

**Avoid:** DataServices mode when entity never used for OData.

### Sensitive field (pay rate, bank account)

**Recommend:** **Table Permissions Framework** — enforced at AOS for all paths.

**Avoid:** `visible(false)` on form control only.

### Row-level filter by org/unit/cust group

**Recommend:** **XDS** policy with minimal join set; constrained tables list; Trace Parser validation; diagnostic bypass role.

**Avoid:** Broad XDS joining many tables on every read of base table.

### Customize permissions for existing role template

**Recommend:** Copy standard role to `MyPub_*` → add duties to copy.

**Avoid:** Edit `Accounts receivable clerk` or other standard role in place.

## Entry point example

```xpp
// BAD
// MenuItem MyPub_ExportOrders — no SecurityPrivilege

// GOOD
// Privilege MyPub_ExportOrdersMaintain → MenuItem MyPub_ExportOrders (Read)
// Duty MyPub_OrderManagementDuty → includes privilege
// Role MyPub_OrderClerkRole → includes duty
```

